# EZ Encode

## About
**EZ Encode** is an attempt at making a custom simple encoder / decoder just for fun.
It has a *two* layer encoding mechanism that allows for a bit more security, though
the conecpt could be improved upon, it still works.

## How It Works

```python
# import the Encode and Decode classes
from ezencode.encoder import Encode
from ezencode.decoder import Decode

# Generate some text to encode
text = "Hello, world! The encoder and decoder really works. \n\n"

# Encode the text
encoder = Encode(text)
encoded = encoder.encoded_text()  # get the encoded text

# Decode the text
decoder = Decode(encoded)
decoded = decoder.decoded_text()  # get the decoded text

print("Encoded: ", encoded, end="\n")  # print the encoded text
print("Decoded: ", decoded, end="\n")  # print the decoded text
```
